#N canvas 0 0 900 460 12;
#X text 20 16 state-table.pd -- maps shrine-state to the tonal mode (the conductor's modal arc).;
#X text 20 40 Per State_Machine: the conductor owns ARRANGEMENT only -- mode/palette/sections.;
#X text 20 58 Continuous expression (gain\, intensity\, tempo\, reverb) is Pd's sensor-driven job\, not the conductor's -- so mode is the one scene->Pd audio lever.;
#X text 20 82 Emits the mode name on [s scene-mode] at each state change (+ loadbang default = quiet's mode). mode-table.pd receives via [r scene-mode].;
#X text 20 120 arc: 0 quiet major-penta | 1 seeking major-penta | 2 aligning dorian | 3 energizing mixolydian-b6 | 4 ascending ionian;
#X obj 40 200 r shrine-state;
#X obj 40 240 sel 0 1 2 3 4;
#X obj 190 240 loadbang;
#X msg 40 300 major-penta;
#X msg 230 300 dorian;
#X msg 380 300 mixolydian-b6;
#X msg 560 300 ionian;
#X obj 40 370 s scene-mode;
#X connect 5 0 6 0;
#X connect 7 0 8 0;
#X connect 6 0 8 0;
#X connect 6 1 8 0;
#X connect 6 2 9 0;
#X connect 6 3 10 0;
#X connect 6 4 11 0;
#X connect 8 0 12 0;
#X connect 9 0 12 0;
#X connect 10 0 12 0;
#X connect 11 0 12 0;
